A PLANE carrying Scots holidaymakers from Edinburgh to Spain was diverted to London after declaring an emergency this morning.
The Jet2 plane took off from Edinburgh airport at 8.30am this morning but an hour into the flight air traffic controllers received an emergency call from the pilots.
It's believed to be a medical issue on board involving a passenger who has become unwell.
 

Emergency services at Gatwick were on standby waiting for the plane to land, which is did shortly before 10am.
